main event: A ground witness observed a small, round object passing overhead at high speed and high altitude in Watertown, Connecticut on September 29, 1961.
interesting points: The object moved from west to east at a high speed and very high altitude.
The witness was an employee on the scene field under the U.S. Government.
Other witnesses on the scene field also observed the object.
The witness was greatly impressed by the performance of the object.
The Air Force's UFO Project Officer responded to the witness, stating they could not provide any information about the identity of the object due to the limited observational data.
witnesses: an employee on the scene field under the U.S. Government and other workers on the scene
